summary: I don’t know why, but I really like the concept of winged characters. I also like the design of wings and how they can be...
caption: I don’t know why, but I really like the concept of winged characters. I also like the design of wings and how they can be incorporated into almost anything as long as anatomy is considered. I also really like drawing wings because of how interesting wings are put together. I liked also, designing how people live if they had wings such as the how the clothes would be designed and how their homes would be built.

summary: OTP drawing challenge! February is coming soon and so is my challenge!! Like every year, I will try to draw something related to...
caption:
OTP drawing challenge!

February is coming soon and so is my challenge!! Like every year, I will try to draw something related to one of my favorite ships every day of the month (which I already know won’t happen but it’s a challenge so I’ll try my best ;p)

For my new followers, I’ve done this challenge each February since I started having a tumblr and it has always helped me improve my art! 

So if this seems interesting and you are, just like me, involved in too many ships and love to draw/write/do gifs/ect. feel free to do the challenge as well: I’d love to see how talented you all are ;0 !!

To participate, you only have to post something concerning a ship you love once a day and tag me if you want so I can see it ;p

summary: FROM THE ARTIST DIRECTORY Engraved Illustrations Catie O’Leary writes, "After seeing a Jess exhibition at the Berkeley Art...
caption:
FROM THE ARTIST DIRECTORY

Engraved Illustrations

Catie O’Leary writes, “After seeing a Jess exhibition at the Berkeley Art Museum, I abandoned all other art forms for collage. The engraved illustrations are my material as well as my inspiration…Each collage is densely composed and like a novel, it takes time to read the intimate yet abstract narratives. The unexpected juxtapositions become embellished maps, poetic landscapes combining the elements of nature and man.” MORE

Kolaj #24 is now available. Our goal with every printed issue is that Kolaj Magazine is essential reading for anyone interested in the role of contemporary collage in art, culture, and society. Kolaj #24 is no different.
